   - Controller class + method name + line number
   - Consumes / Produces media types
   - Auth/security annotations (@PreAuthorize, @Secured, filters)

2. **Request Breakdown**
   - Path variables (name, type, constraints)
   - Query params (name, type, required?, default)
   - Request headers read
   - Request body: full DTO class name + every field (name, type, validation annotations like @NotNull, @Size, @Pattern)
   - Any @RequestPart / multipart handling

3. **Execution Flow (step by step)**
   - List every method call made from the controller method, in order
   - For each call: which service/repository/external client it hits, what it does, what it returns
   - Note every branch (if/else, switch, try/catch) and what each path does
   - Note transactions (@Transactional), async (@Async), caching (@Cacheable)

4. **Response Breakdown**
   - Success HTTP status (200/201/204/etc.)
   - Response body: full DTO + every field (type, nullable?)
   - Response headers set
   - ResponseEntity wrapping behavior

5. **Error Paths**
   - Every exception that can be thrown from this flow
   - Matching @ExceptionHandler / @ControllerAdvice behavior
   - Resulting HTTP status + error body shape for each

6. **External Dependencies Touched**
   - Database tables / entities
   - External HTTP calls (URL, method, payload)
   - Message queues, caches, file system

7. **Unknowns / Flagged Items**
   - Anything referenced but not visible in this file (mark as `[needs file: X]`)
   - Suspicious patterns, missing validation, potential bugs
